
[1]catoptromancy

   CATOPTROMANCY, n. A species of divination among the ancients, which was
   performed by letting down a mirror into water, for a sick person to
   look at his face in it. If his countenance appeared distorted and
   ghastly, it was an ill omen; if fresh and healthy, it was favorable.
